@{
	ViewBag.Title = Piranha.Resources.Account.InstallTitle;
	Layout = "";
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
	<title>Wecome to Piranha CMS</title>

	<link href="~/res.ashx/areas/manager/content/img/icon.ico" rel="icon" type="image/x-icon">
	<link href="~/res.ashx/areas/manager/content/img/icon.ico" rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon">
	<link href="~/res.ashx/areas/manager/content/css/style.min.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />

	<style type="text/css">
		.grid_12.welcome {
			font-size: 108%;
		}

		.welcome .title {
			padding: 20px 34px;
		}
		.welcome .title h2 {
			font-size: 24px;
		}

		.welcome .inner hr {
			color: #ddd;
			background: #ddd;
			border: 0;
			height: 1px;
			margin-bottom: 14px;
		}

		.welcome .inner {
			padding: 24px 34px;
			background: url('@Href("~/res.ashx/areas/manager/content/img/logo-big.png")') no-repeat 190% -10%;
		}

		.welcome .inner p {
			padding-bottom: 14px;
			line-height: 1.4em;
		}

		.welcome .inner h2 {
			border-bottom: 1px solid #DDDDDD;
			font-size: 20px;
			font-weight: bold;
			margin: 10px 0;
			padding-bottom: 8px;
		}

		.welcome .inner pre {
			padding-bottom: 14px;
		}

		.welcome .inner code {
			font-size: 14px;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container_12">
		<div class="grid_12 box welcome">
			<div class="title"><h2>Welcome to Piranha CMS</h2></div>
			<div class="inner">
				<p>
					Hi, and welcome to Piranha CMS. We're assuming that this is the <strong>first</strong> time
					you start your application since there's no connection string configured with the
					name <code>piranha</code>.
				</p>

				<p>
					If you take a look in your web.config you'll see that there's example connection
					strings included for <code>SqlCE</code>, <code>SqlExpress</code>, <code>LocalDb</code> and
					<code>SqlServer</code>.
				</p>

				<h2>SqlCE</h2>

				<p>
					If you want to use SqlCE, which is a file-based database hosted in your web
					application you have to start by installing the following package from NuGet:
				</p>

				<pre><code>&gt; Install-Package EntityFramework.SqlServerCompact</code></pre>

				<p>
					After this is done, rename the connection string named <strong>piranha-ce</strong>
					to <strong>piranha</strong> and if you wish, modify the name and location of
					your <code>.sdf</code> file.
				</p>

				<h2>SqlExpress</h2>

				<p>
					If you want to use SqlExpress, which is a free, out-of-process database, rename the
					connection string named <strong>piranha-express</strong> to <strong>piranha</strong>
					and change the credentials to real values. Make sure you <strong>create</strong> the database
					before continuing as the installer only installs the Schema and default data, it does not
					create the database for you.
				</p>

				<h2>LocalDb</h2>

				<p>
					If you want to use LocalDb, which is a free, in-process development database, rename the
					connection string named <strong>piranha-local</strong> to <strong>piranha</strong> and
					change the credentials to real values. Make sure you <strong>create</strong> the database
					before continuing as the installer only installs the Schema and default data, it does not
					create the database for you.
				</p>

				<h2>SqlServer</h2>

				<p>
					If you want to use SqlServer, which is Microsofts production-line database, rename the
					connection string named <strong>piranha-sql</strong> to <strong>piranha</strong> and change
					the credentials to real values. Make sure you <strong>create</strong> the database before
					continuing as the installer only installs the Schema and default data, it does not create
					the database for you.
				</p>

				<hr />
				<p>
					After you have configured your database you can <a href="@Url.Action("index")">continue</a> to the installation.
				</p>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>